ENTP | INTP | ENTJ | INTJ

The Doer:
Focus on the here and now

The Performer:
If there's no excitement, we'll create it

labels:
Introverted Sensing Thinking Perceiving (ISTP)

Acronym : I See The Problem

ISTP's excel at analyzing situations to reach the heart of a problem so that they can swiftly
implement a functional repair, making them ideally suited to the field of engineering.

ISTP's are often capable of humorously insightful observations about the world around them.

ISTP's may sometimes seem to act without regard for procedures, directions, protocol,
or even their own safety. But while their approach may seem haphazard, it is in fact based
on a broad store of knowledge developed over time.

Compelled to understand how things work.
Are loyal to their causes and beliefs.
Like to be up and about, doing things.
ISTPs are excellent in a crisis situations.

Construction, Electrician, Factory Worker,
Mechanic, Military, Pilot

More (The Builder) :
Carpenter, Commercial Artist, Firefighter,
Geologist, Mechanic, Surveyor, Intelligence Agent

Amelia Earhart, Christian Bale, Chuck Yeager, Clint Eastwood,
Demi Moore, Eazy-E, Harrison Ford, Sally Ride, Simon Cowell,
Steve Jobs, Tom Cruise, Venus Williams, Vladimir Putin

If at first you don't succeed, try, try, again. Then quit.
There's no point in being a damn fool about it.
- W.C. Fields

Extraverted Sensing Thinking Perceiving (ESTP)

Acronym : Extraordinarily Smooth Talking Persuader

ESTP's are hands-on learners who live in the moment, seeking the best in life,
wanting to share it with their friends.

ESTP's are high energy extroverts who maximize each moment to get the best out of life.
They are gregarious and sociable which often makes them the center or attention
whether they are at work or a social event.

An ESTP will be a natural group leader who can quickly identify the strengths
and weaknesses of each member of their team.

ESTPs are outgoing, straight-shooting types.
Live in the world of action.
Place little importance on theory.
Are action-oriented, make decisions quickly.

Construction Worker, Entrepeneur,
Firefighter, Paramedic, Sales

More (The Doer) :
Entrepreneur, Pilot, Police Officer, Pro Athlete,
General Contractor, Promoter, Stockbroker

Al Capone, Alexander the Great, Donald Trump, Epicurus,
Franklin Roosevelt, Kevin Spacey, L. Ron Hubbard, Madonna,
Malcolm X, Mike Tyson, Milla Jovovich, Winston Churchill

Action may not always bring happiness,
but there is no happiness without action.
- William James

Intoverted Sensing Feeling Perceiving (ISFP)

Acronym : I'm Sincerely Fulfilling my Purpose

ISFP's are peaceful, easygoing people who adopt a "live and let live" approach to life.
They enjoy taking things at their own pace and tend to live in the moment.

ISFP's are difficult to build a close relationship with. They usually have a small
circle of friends and family who they have had relationships with
over long periods of time.

They excel in positions where they can follow their own personal value
system while also expressing themselves creatively.

Keenly in tune with the outside world.
Kind and sensitive with regard to others.
Truly appreciate the beauties of nature.
ISFPs are action-oriented individuals.

Designer, Elementary, Teacher,
Musician, Nurse, Social Worker

More (The Artist) :
Archaeologist, Dancer, Forestry, Painter,
Beautician, Chef, Landscape Architect

Audrey Hepburn, Christopher Reeve, David Beckham, Elizabeth Taylor,
Heath Ledger, Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis, Jessica Alba, Marie Antoinette,
Marilyn Monroe, Mark McGwire, Michael Jackson, Neil Simon,
Paul McCartney, Prince, Ulysses S. Grant

Sometimes its not there strength but gentleness
that cracks the hardest shells.
- Richard Paul Evans

Extraverted Sensing Feeling Perceiving (ESFP)

Acronym : Entertaining, Sparkly, Friendly Person

ESFP's live in the moment, experiencing life to the fullest. They enjoy
people, as well as material comforts.

Rarely allowing conventions to interfere with their lives, they find
creative ways to meet human needs.

Observant, practical, realistic, and specific, ESFP's make decisions according to their own
personal standards. They use their Feeling judgment internally to identify and
empathize with others. Naturally attentive to the world around them.

Love people and new experiences.
Also like to have fun.
Warm and generous with their friends.
Have a great love for life.

Actor, Coach, Receptionist, Painter,
Personal Trainer, Salesperson

More (The Performer) :
Film Producer, Sales Rep, Stockbroker, Waiter/Waitress,
Travel Agent, Real Estate Agent, Receptionist

Andy Sandberg, Benito Mussolini, Bill Clinton, Chloe Grace Moretz,
Deepak Chopra, John F. Kennedy, Katy Perry, Kyle Petty,
Michelangelo Buonarroti, Serena Williams,
Stephen Spielberg, Tony Robbins

I just like having fun. And, you know, sometimes i just like to
present myself in that fun energy.
- Katy Perry

Introverted Sensing Thinking Judging (ISTJ)

Acronym : I Suit Tax Jobs

ISTJ's thrive on organization. They keep their lives and environments well-regulated.
They bring painstaking attention to detail in their work and will not
rest until a job is well completed.

ISTJ's are faithful, logical, organized, sensible, and earnest traditionalists.
They earn success by thoroughness and dependability.

ISTJ's respect facts. They hold a tremendous store of data within
themselves, gathered through their Sensing function.

ISTJs are loyal, faithful, and dependable.
Tend to believe in laws and traditions.
May have difficulty picking up emotions.
Want their personal lives to run smoothly.

Accountant, Dentist, Math Teacher,
Office Administrator, Police

More (The Realist) :
Accountant, Government, Military Officer, Auditor,
Business Analyst, Physician, Librarian

Condoleeza Rice, Evander Holyfield, George Washington,
Julia Roberts, Pope Benedict, Queen Elizabeth II, Richard Nixon,
Robert De Niro, Sigmund Freud, Sting, Stonewall Jackson, Warren Buffett

He who labors diligently need never despair; for all
things are accomplished by diligence and labor.
- Menander

Extraverted Sensing Thinking Judging (ESTJ)

Acronym : Elevated Stress Tightens Jaw

ESTJ's are practical, realistic, and matter-of-fact, with a natural
head for business or mechanics.

ESTJ's take a practical approach to life that is guided by their matter-of-fact
attitudes and focus on realism. They recognize tradition and prefer
order which makes them strong leaders.

They abhor laziness and cheating, and instead stick to their principles with
unclouded judgment. They are often described by others
as charismatic, focused and driven.

They naturally step into leadership roles.
Live in a world of facts and concrete needs.
The ESTJ is usually a model citizen.
Potential to become overly detail-oriented.

Business Administrator, Financial Officer,
Office Manager, Military

More (The Administrator) :
Bank Manager, Judge, Lawyer, Prison Warden
Athletic Director, School principal, Policeman

Andrew Jackson, Ann Coulter, Augusto Pinochet, Billy Graham,
Daisy Ridley, Henry Ford, Hillary Clinton, Ivanka Trump,
John Smoltz, Judge Judy, Martha Stewart, Saddam Hussein

In my mind nothing is more abhorrent that a life of ease. ...
There is no place in civilization for the idler.
- Henry Ford

Introverted Sensing Feeling Judging (ISFJ)

Acronym : I Serve my Family Joyfully

ISFJ's are interested in maintaining order and harmony in every aspect of their lives.
They are steadfast and meticulous in handling their responsibilities.

ISFJ's are warm-hearted and compassionate individuals who are
always thinking of others before themselves.

Emotionally oriented, ISFJ's are sensitive to other people's
feelings and have a deep understanding of their own.

ISFJs want to believe the best of people.
Have a rich but hidden inner world.
ISFJs respect traditions and laws.
Do not usually express their own feelings.

Clergy, Interior Decorator, Librarian,
Nurse, Office Administrator

More (The Protector) :
Historian, Nurse, Minister, Paralegal,
Physical Therapist, Teacher, Social Worker

Jimmy Carter, Kate Middleton, Rosa Parks,
Mother Teresa, Tiger Woods

So long as we love we serve; so long as we are loved by others,
i would almost say that we are indispensable.
- Robert Louis Stevenson

Extraverted Sensing Feeling Judging (ESFJ)

Acronym : Especially Satisfied Fulfilling Jobs

ESFJ's focus on the outside world and assess their experiences subjectively.

They largely base their judgments on their belief system and on the effects of
actions on people. ESFJ's are literal and concrete, trusting the specific,
factual information gathered through their physiological senses.

ESFJ's project warmth through a genuine interest in the well-being of others.
They are often skilled at bringing out the best in people,
and they want to understand other points of view.

Are people persons - they love people.
Take their responsibilities very seriously.
Get satisfaction others' happiness.
Have a strong community-based moral code.

Nurse, Office Administrator,
Social Worker, Teacher

More (The Helper) :
Personal Trailer, Funeral Director, Court Reporter,
Athletic Coach, Flight Attendant, Legal Assistant,
Childcare Provider

Andrew Carnegie, Barbara Walters, Desmond Tutu, Elton John,
Nancy Kerrigan, Prince William, Pope Francis, Whitney Houston

Happiness is only real when it is shared.
- Jon Krakauer

Extraverted Intuitive Thinking Perceiving (ENTP)

Acronym : Every New Thought Propels

ENTP's are quick to see complex interrelationships between people, things,
and ideas and are able to analyze these interrelationships in profound detail.

ENTP's are frequently described as clever, cerebrally and verbally quick,
enthusiastic, outgoing, innovative, flexible, loyal and resourceful.

ENTP's are motivated by a desire to understand and improve the world they live in.
They are usually accurate in sizing up a situation. They may have a perverse
sense of humor and sometimes play devil's advocate.

Can see possibilities everywhere.
Size up situations quickly.
Love to debate ideas.
Able to spread their enthusiasm to others.

Engineer, Entrepeneur, Inventor,
Lawyer, Scientist

More (The Inventor) :
Market Researcher, Venture Capitalist, Strategic Planner,
HR Manager, Producer, City Planner, Hotel Manager

Amy Poehler, Barack Obama, Ben Franklin, Harry Connick Jr,
Leonardo Da Vinci, Neil Patrick Harris, Sir Walter Raleigh,
Stephen Colbert, Steve Wozniak, Theodore Roosevelt

It is better to deabate a question without settling it
thatto settle a question without debating it.
- Joseph Joubert

Introverted Intuitive Thinking Perceiving (INTP)

Acronym : I Need To Ponder

INTP's are quiet, thoughtful, analytical individuals who tend to spend long periods
of time on their own, working through problems and forming solutions.

They generally balk at attempts by others to convince them to change.
They also tend to be impatient with the bureaucracy, rigid hierarchies,
and the politics prevalent in many professions.

INTP's organize their understanding of any topic by articulating principles,
and they are especially drawn to theoretical constructs.

Live in the world of theoretical possibilities.
INTPs are driven to build knowledge.
Do not like to lead or control people.
Usually not in-tune with people's feelings.

Engineer, College Professor, Psychologist,
Researcher, Scientist

More (The Scientist) :
College Professor, Mathematician, Financial Analyst,
Chemist, Lawyer/Judge, Researcher, Physicist

Albert Einstein, Carl Jung, Charles Darwin, Ellen Page,
George Soros, Jimmy Wales, Larry Page, Liam Gallagher,
M.I.A, Thucydides, Tina Fey

If i had an hour to solve a problem i'd spend 55 minutes thing about
the problem and 5 minutes thingking about solutions.
- Albert Einstein

Extraverted Intuitive Thinking Judging (ENTJ)

Acronym : Executives Navigating Tough Jobs

ENTJ's focus on the most efficient and organized means of performing a task.
This quality, along with their goal orientation, often makes ENTJ's superior
leaders, both realistic and visionary in implementing a long-term plan.

ENTJ's tend to be fiercely independent in their decision making, having
a strong will that insulates them against external influence.

Generally highly competent, ENTJ's analyze and structure
the world around them in a logical and rational way.

Are natural born leaders.
Dislike seeing mistakes repeated.
Are very forceful and decisive.
Love interacting with people.

Administrator, CEO, Entrepreneur,
Lawyer, Judge, Manager

More (The Commander) :
CEO, Judge, Business Consultant, Sales Manager,
Actor, Politician, Administrator

Bill Gates, Carl Sagan, Julius Caesar, Madeleine Albright,
Margaret Thatcher, Napoleon Bonaparte

Live your vision and demand your success.
- Steve Maraboli

Introverted Intuitive Thinking Judging (INTJ)

Acronym : It's Not Thoroughly Justified

INTJ's are analytical. They are most comfortable working alone and
tend to be less sociable than other types.

They have a low tolerance for spin or rampant emotionalism. They are not
generally susceptible to catchphrases and do not recognize
authority based on tradition, rank, or title.

They harbor an innate desire to express themselves by conceptualizing
their own intellectual designs. They have a talent for analyzing
and formulating complex theories.

Value intelligence, knowledge and competence.
Focus on generating ideas and possibilities.
Not easy for the INTJ to express their insights.
Spend a lot of time inside their own minds.

Programmer, Scientist, Corporate Strategist, Doctor, Engineer

More (The Mastermind) :
Programmer, Scientist, Database Admin, Astronomer,
Economist, Aerospace Engineer, Financial Analyst

Ayn Rand, Bobby Fischer, Dwight D. Eisenhower, Jane Austen,
Jay Z, Karl Marx, Mark Zuckerberg, Martin Luther,
Sir Isaac Newton, Stephen Hawking

There's always room for improvement, you know -
it's the biggest room in the house.
- Louise Heath Leber

Extraverted Intuitive Feeling Perceiving (ENFP)

Acronym : Eagerly Noting Fun Playgrounds

ENFP's are initiators of change, keenly perceptive of possibilities. They energize
and stimulate others through their Contagious enthusiasm.

They prefer the start-up phase of a project or relationship, and are
tireless in the pursuit of new-found interests.

ENFP's are able to anticipate the needs of others and to offer them needed
help and appreciation. They bring zest, joy, liveliness, and
fun to all aspects of their lives.

Have a broad range of skills and talents.
They are warm and interested in people.
They have a strong need to be independent.
Very passionate about things and ideas.

Actor, Counselor, Journalist, Politician, Teacher, Writer

More (The Champion) :
Charity Director, Character Actor, Event Planner,
Public Relations, News Anchor, Spokesperson, Journalist

Ellen DeGeneres, George Carlin, J.J. Abrams, Jennifer Anniston,
Jerry Seinfeld, Julian Assange, Mark Twain, Orson Welles,
Salman Rushdie, Walt Disney

Ideas can be life-changing. Sometimes all you need
to open the door is just one more good idea.
- Jim Rohn

Introverted Intuitive Feeling Perceiving (INFP)

Acronym : Ideals Need Faithful Pursuit

The polite, reserved exterior of INFP's can at first make them difficult to get to know.
They enjoy conversation, however, taking particular delight in the unusual.

Devoted to those in their inner circle, INFP's guard the emotional well-being of others,
consoling those in distress. Guided by their desire for harmony,
INFP's prefer to be flexible unless their ethics are violated.

Though not always organized, INFP's are meticulous about things they value.

Main goal is to find out their meaning in life.
Are good listeners and put people at ease.
Very high standards and are perfectionists.
Will fight passionately for their "cause".

Artist, Counselor, Editor, Musician,
Political Activist, Teacher, Writer

More (The Mediator) :
Missionary, Curator, College Professor,
Actor, Composer, Teacher, Counselor

A. A. Milne, Albert Schweitzer, Andy Warhol, Chloe Sevigny,
Chris Martin, Hellen Keller, John Lennon, Kurt Cobain,
Tom Hiddleston, Vincent Van Gogh, William Shakespeare

If you light a lamp for somebody, it will also brighten your path.
- Buddhist Saying

Extraverted Intuitive Feeling Judging (ENFJ)

Acronym : Everyone Needs Fulfillment & Joy

ENFJ's seek continuity through harmonious relationships and collective values.
The excel at picking up on the tone of a situation and acting accordingly,
adding warmth to a cool setting or turning sour into sweet.

They are natural cheerleaders, often expressing support, gratitude,
and encouragement, and heaping praise onto those they appreciate.
They take note of what is being done and what needs doing,
offering their assistance wherever necessary.

Have many friends and close relationships.
Sensitive to those who feel excluded.
Enjoy organizing group activities.
Loyal and expect loyalty in return.

Business Consultant, HR Manager,
Teacher, Writer

More (The Teacher) :
Recruiter, Teacher, Consultant, Reporter,
Restaurant Manager, Translator, Writer

Bono, Martin Luther King Jr, Nelson Mandela,
Opra Winfrey, Pope John Paul II

Enthusiasm speels the difference between
mediocrity and accomplishment.
- Normal Vincent Peale

Introverted Intuitive Feeling Judging (INFJ)

Acronym : Inner Nuances Foster Journeys

INFJ's are conscientious and value-driven. They seek meaning in relationships, ideas,
and events, with an eye toward better understanding themselves and others.

INFJ's are quiet, private individuals who prefer to exercise their influence behind the scenes.

INFJ's have a rich, vivid inner life, which they may be reluctant to share with those around them.
Abstract in communicating, they live in a world of hidden meanings and possibilities.

INFJs are gentle, caring and complex.
Have deep insight into people and situations.
As genuinely warm as they are complex.
INFJ are nurturers; patient and devoted.

Artist, Clergy, Counselor, Photographer,
Teacher, Writer

More (The Advocate) :
Psychologist, Counselor, Social Worker, Mediator,
Minister, Human Resources, Massage Therapist

Adolf Hitler, Alanis Morissette, Jane Goodall, Leonard Cohen,
Ludwig Wittgenstein, Mahatma Gandhi, Marilyn Manson,
Martin Van Buren, Noam Chomsky, Taylor Swift, Thomas Jefferson

If you have a dream, don't just sit there. Gather courage to believe that
you can succeed and leave no stone unturned to make it a reality.
- Roopleen
